Download the latest Raspbian "wheezy" image from http://www.raspberrypi.org/downloads

Flash the OS image to your SD card. See http://elinux.org/RPi_Easy_SD_Card_Setup for help
(Gives an error after ~10 minutes on Mac os x. The card works anyways)

Connect screen, keyboard, SD card and power to your RasPi.

After a while, Raspberry config should appear.

Expand Filesystem -> Ok
Advanced options -> SSH -> Enable -> Ok
Finish -> Yes

RasPi reboots now

Default login credentials are:
  login: pi
  password: raspberry

Find out the IP-address of your RasPi
  login
  ifconfig
  inet addr:***.***.***.*** <- RasPi's IP-address

Connect to your RasPi with SSH

turn on IPv6 support:
  sudo modprobe ipv6
  echo ipv6 | sudo tee -a /etc/modules

install mopidy:
  wget -q -O - http://apt.mopidy.com/mopidy.gpg | sudo apt-key add -
  sudo wget -q -O /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mopidy.list http://apt.mopidy.com/mopidy.list
  sudo apt-get update
  sudo apt-get install mopidy

configure mopidy:
  
  Create config file for mopidy

  mkdir -p ~/.config/mopidy
  nano ~/.config/mopidy/mopidy.conf

  Paste configuration to the file and insert your own values

  [spotify]
  username = username (example 1133600000)
  password = password

  [local]
  enabled = false

  [scrobbler]
  username = username
  password = password

  [http]
  hostname = ::
  static_dir = /home/pi/mopidy-webclient/public/

install mopidy webclient:
cd ~/
git clone git@github.com:rikukissa/mopidy-webclient.git

start mopidy and the webclient:
mopidy


